Proxies

Proxies : In behalf


           forward
          -------->
Client    [ Proxy ]     Server
          <--------
           reverse


In Term of client-server Arch
- Forward Proxy
    Machine sit between client and server side that sits on server, which talk's to a server on behalf of client
    Client never talk to server ( client is anonymous to server )
    Proxy talk to server

    Eg :
     Block the site

- Reverse Proxy
    Machine sit between client and server side that sits on server, which talk's to a client on behalf of server
    Client talk to proxy
    Proxy talk to client

    Eg :
    Traffic Control
    Caching Response
    Mitigate DDos Attack
    SSL Encryption

